FBIS4-58116 "drnes084_c_94005" FBIS-NES-94-084 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 Egypt Mubarak Receives Call From Yemen's al-Bid Mubarak Receives Call From Yemen's al-Bid NC2904192294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in Arabic 1830 GMT 29 Apr 94 NC2904192294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] President Husni Mubarak received a telephone call this evening from Yemeni Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, during which he explained to the president the worsening situation in fraternal Yemen. President Mubarak requested that the Yemeni parties end the fighting, solve the crisis through mutual understanding, and respond to the Egyptian and Arab peace efforts to safeguard the supreme interests of the fraternal Yemeni people. Meanwhile, southern Yemeni sources have stated that fighting broke out again today between the southern and northern military units, and extended to southern areas of Yemen. The sources added that the current fighting is taking place in the southern provinces of Abyan and Lahij. The Yemeni Defense Ministry in Sanaa said in a statement today that the southern forces deployed in the Dhamar base, south of Sanaa, have left their camps and have taken up positions in the surrounding areas on the orders of the leaders of the Socialist Party to aggravate the military situation in Yemen. Informed sources in Sanaa said that an extensive search is under way in the Amran camp area, north of Sanaa, which witnessed heavy fighting last Wednesday and Thursday [27-28 April], for Colonel Sayf al-Baqari, commander of the southern 3rd Armored brigade, to bring him to court martial for issuing the orders to start the fighting in the area.
